n        \u003c/header\u003e\n\n        \u003cdiv class=\"slot-window\"\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"reel\" id=\"reel1\"\u003e🤖\u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"reel\" id=\"reel2\"\u003e🤖\u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"reel\" id=\"reel3\"\u003e🤖\u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n        \u003cdiv class=\"controls\"\u003e\n            \u003cbutton id=\"spin-button\"\u003eBurn 10 Tokens\u003c/button\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n        \u003cdiv class=\"status-box\"\u003e\n            \u003cp id=\"message\"\u003ePress \"Burn\" to start inferencing...\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n        \u003cdiv class=\"ai-logs\"\u003e\n            \u003csmall\u003eSystem Log: \u003cspan id=\"log-text\"\u003eAwaiting prompt...\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/small\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cscript src=\"script.js\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e\n\u003c/body\u003e\n\u003c/html\u003e\n```\n\n#### 2. The Styling (CSS)\nWe use `flexbox` for alignment and a CSS transition for the \"spinning\" blur effect.\n\n```css\n:root {\n    --primary: #00ffcc;\n    --bg: #1a1a1a;\n    --panel: #2d2d2d;\n    --text: #ffffff;\n}\n\nbody {\n    background-color: var(--bg);\n    color: var(--text);\n    font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: center;\n    align-items: center;\n    height: 100vh;\n    margin: 0;\n}\n\n.machine-container {\n    background: var(--panel);\n    padding: 2rem;\n    border-radius: 15px;\n    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 255, 204, 0.2);\n    text-align: center;\n    width: 350px;\n}\n\n.slot-window {\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 10px;\n    background: #000;\n    padding: 20px;\n    border-radius: 10px;\n    margin: 20px 0;\n    justify-content: center;\n    border: 2px solid #444;\n}\n\n.reel {\n    font-size: 3rem;\n    width: 80px;\n    height: 80px;\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: center;\n    align-items: center;\n    background: #222;\n    border-radius: 5px;\n    transition: transform 0.1s ease-out;\n}\n\n.spinning {\n    filter: blur(4px);\n    transform: scale(0.9);\n}\n\nbutton {\n    background: var(--primary);\n    border: none;\n    padding: 15px 30px;\n    font-weight: bold;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    border-radius: 5px;\n    transition: 0.2s;\n}\n\nbutton:disabled {\n    background: #555;\n    cursor: not-allowed;\n}\n\n.status-box {\n    margin-top: 15px;\n    min-height: 50px;\n    color: var(--primary);\n}\n\n.ai-logs {\n    margin-top: 20px;\n    color: #888;\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n    border-top: 1px solid #444;\n    padding-top: 10px;\n}\n```\n\n#### 3. The Logic (JavaScript)\nThis script handles the \"randomness\" and the AI-themed status updates.\n\n```javascript\nconst symbols = ['🤖', '🍄', '📟', '💸', '🧠', '🌌'];\nconst winMessages = [\n    \"AGI achieved! (Actually just a better lookup table)\",\n    \"Hallucination successful! Here are some fake facts.\",\n    \"VC funding secured. Burn those tokens!\",\n    \"Scaling laws hold true. More GPUs needed.\"\n];\nconst failMessages = [\n    \"Model collapsed. Try a longer prompt.\",\n    \"Token limit reached. Buy more credits.\",\n    \"The AI is tired. Ask something easier.\",\n    \"404: Logic not found in training data.\"\n];\n\nlet tokens = 500;\nconst spinCost = 10;\n\nconst spinBtn = document.getElementById('spin-button');\nconst tokenDisplay = document.getElementById('token-count');\nconst reels = [document.getElementById('reel1'), document.getElementById('reel2'), document.getElementById('reel3')];\nconst message = document.getElementById('message');\nconst logText = document.getElementById('log-text');\n\nfunction getRandomSymbol() {\n    return symbols[Math.floor(Math.random() * symbols.length)];\n}\n\nasync function spin() {\n    if (tokens \u003c spinCost) {\n        message.innerText = \"Insufficient tokens. Please insert more GPU hours.\";\n        return;\n    }\n\n    // Spend tokens\n    tokens -= spinCost;\n    updateUI();\n    \n    spinBtn.disabled = true;\n    message.innerText = \"Inferencing...\";\n    logText.innerText = \"Calculating weights...\";\n\n    // Visual Spin Effect\n    reels.forEach(reel =\u003e reel.classList.add('spinning'));\n\n    // Simulation of network latency/compute time\n    await new Promise(resolve =\u003e setTimeout(resolve, 1200));\n\n    const results = reels.map(reel =\u003e {\n        const symbol = getRandomSymbol();\n        reel.innerText = symbol;\n        reel.classList.remove('spinning');\n        return symbol;\n    });\n\n    resolveGame(results);\n}\n\nfunction resolveGame(results) {\n    const isWin = results[0] === results[1] \u0026\u0026 results[1] === results[2];\n    \n    if (isWin) {\n        const reward = 200;\n        tokens += reward;\n        message.innerText = winMessages[Math.floor(Math.random() * winMessages.length)];\n        logText.innerText = `Reward: +${reward} tokens. High confidence interval.`;\n    } else {\n        message.innerText = failMessages[Math.floor(Math.random() * failMessages.length)];\n        logText.innerText = \"Stochastic parity check failed.\";\n    }\n\n    updateUI();\n    spinBtn.disabled = false;\n}\n\nfunction updateUI() {\n    tokenDisplay.innerText = tokens;\n}\n\nspinBtn.addEventListener('click', spin);\n```\n\n### Review \u0026 Suggestions\n\n1.  **Modular State:** For a production app, I would recommend moving the symbols and messages into a separate configuration file or object to make the logic easier to maintain.\n2.  **Animation Improvements:** Instead of a simple blur, you could use a `requestAnimationFrame` loop to actually cycle through icons rapidly. This creates a more authentic \"rolling\" reel effect.\n3.  **Accessibility:** Ensure the status messages are announced to screen readers by using `aria-live=\"polite\"` on the status-box element.\n\n\u003c!--\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]How can I add a high-score leaderboard using the browser's localStorage? [/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]Can you rewrite the spin animation to use the Web Animations API for a smoother scrolling effect?[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n--\u003e","chatSectionId":"3","ideContext":{"currentFile":{"path":"","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0}},"remoteContexts":null,"remoteRepositories":[],"otherFiles":null,"rules":null,"editableRegion":null,"recentUserActions":null,"chatSectionId":"3"},"openFileUri":"output:extension-output-google.geminicodeassist-%232-Gemini%20Code%20Assist","ragStatus":"RAG_DISABLED","timeToFirstToken":"16112","agentProcessingDetails":{},"workspaceChange":{},"fileUsage":{},"suggestedPrompts":["How can I add a high-score leaderboard using the browser's localStorage? ","Can you rewrite the spin animation to use the Web Animations API for a smoother scrolling effect?"],"thinkingSummaryMarkdownText":"**Conceptualizing AI Mockery**\n\nI've been envisioning the slot machine's satirical AI theme. I'm focusing on how the tokens are won and spent, framing it to poke fun at AI. The plan is to keep the code neat and the interface intuitive, relying on fundamental web technologies.\n\n\n**Developing the Core Mechanics**\n\nI'm currently focused on the Javascript logic, fleshing out the core mechanics of the slot machine. I'm prioritizing the random symbol generation, implementing win conditions, and managing the token system. I'm exploring various animation techniques for the reels. I want the code to be easy to read and modify, while also making the user experience smooth and interactive.\n\n\n**Constructing the Interface**\n\nI'm now diving into the HTML and CSS. I'm focusing on a simple structure with semantic tags. The CSS will use variables for colors and keyframes for the \"blur\" animation during the spin. The current goal is for the UI to be visually appealing, with a cyberpunk/glassmorphism vibe to satirize AI. The HTML is structured, with display sections for tokens and a status message.\n\n\n**Finalizing Core Elements**\n\nI'm presently building the `spin()` function in Javascript, implementing the token deduction, animation initiation, and the resolution of results. I'm leveraging the provided symbol array. I'll include snarky messages depending on the win condition.\n\n\n","agentMetadata":{"coderAgent":{"kind":""},"model":""},"modelDisplayName":"3 Flash Preview","modelID":"chat-gemini-3-0-flash-preview-free-tier"}],"ragStatus":"RAG_DISABLED","threadId":"1bc7d5cc-3760-11f1-96d8-5e55762ade97"}
